; 4th century BC: Eubulides

* Starting with one grain, and adding grain after grain, no single grain can make the difference between a number of grains and a heap.
* Someone says "What I am now saying is false"; if it is true, it is false; and if it is false, it is true.
* A hooded man enters the room and you do not know who he is, but he is in fact your brother; so you do not know who your brother is